Instructions:

-launch VMEmulator.sh inside the 'tool' directory
 (Linux Users: just cd into tool directory and ./VMEmulator.sh)

-open one of my demos directory (BouncySquare or cli-paint)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

BoucySquare is a simple game, press space to jump and avoid the spikes. Score is
in the top-left corner

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Cli-paint is a simple JackOs demo, you can draw through command line expression.
Syntax:
 ----------------------------
|Color | Shape | Coordinates |
 ----------------------------
|W or B| LINE  | x,y;xx,yy;  |
|W or B| CIRC  | x,y,r;      |
|W or B| PIX   | x,y;        |
|W or B| RECT  | x,y;xx,yy;  |
------------------------------

Examples:
BLINE 0,0;100,100;      <-- draws a Black LINE from (0,0) to (100,100)
WCIRC 100,100,40;       <-- draws a White CIRCle in (100,100) with a 40px radius

!! IMPORTANT !!
There`s no error handling, so if you use a wrong syntax you must restart the
Emulator. If you are getting errors, check the syntax! Don`t forget to put a
semicolon at the end of each command and commas where requested (see table
above). Also spaces are very important, this is not a full feature program but a
demo.
